he `getStylesheet` wrapper, I think `getStylesheet()` should return a `URLResource`. I'll need to make sure to assert that it's not null and perhaps check if it exists. I’m curious if a Resource API will be involved here.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Considering class loading options**\\\\n\\\\nI'm thinking about whether to avoid using a subclass for Class#getResource. It seems like a public subclass in the same package might not be the best route, especially since I’ve read something about keeping tests outside of library packages. Another idea might be to explore using a custom classloader. Alternatively, I could use AggregateTransformer's getClass() if it's not a subclass. I also wonder if `MethodHandles.privateLookupIn` could help with accessing protected members directly.\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_5M1pKS7wGfUyJdMP3b0OrS1i|fc_08e5b7320191e34b016a263c7e52e48194bc103cab7826d250\", \"name\": \"bash\", \"arguments\": {\"command\": \"find metadata/org.apache.ant/ant-junit/1.10.15 -type f -maxdepth 5 -print -exec sh -c 'echo --- $1; sed -n \\\"1,220p\\\" \\\"$1\\\"' sh {} \\\\;\"}}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"oca/gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 2457, \"output\": 1255, \"cacheRead\": 23552, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 27264, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\", \"timestamp\": 1780890727019, \"responseId\": \"resp_08e5b7320191e34b016a263c677b508194879b0889ee011d61\"}}\n../2471-ebd1b0ae/human-intervention-logs/org.apache.ant:ant-junit:1.10.15/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-06-08T03-53-24-554518Z.log:1576:[recv] {\"type\": \"turn_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"thinking\", \"thinking\": \"**Evaluating exception handling**\\n\\nI'm thinking about how to assert a `FileNotFoundException` for the message \\\"junit-noframes.xsl.\\\" That seems fine. I wonder if the dynamic approach in native might also have missing resources, leading to similar exceptions. That’s good to note! Regarding the `getStylesheet` wrapper, I think `getStylesheet()` should return a `URLResource`. I'll need to make sure to assert that it's not null and perhaps check if it exists. I’m curious if a Resource API will be involved here.\\n\\n**Considering class loading options**\\n\\nI'm thinking about whether to avoid using a subclass for Class#getResource. It seems like a public subclass in the same package might not be the best route, especially since I’ve read something about keeping tests outside of library packages. Another idea might be to explore using a custom classloader. Alternatively, I could use AggregateTransformer's getClass() if it's not a subclass. I also wonder if `MethodHandles.privateLookupIn` could help with accessing protected members directly.\", \"thinkingSignature\": \"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"rs_08e5b7320191e34b016a263c68320c81949bd90b51529a39ba\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"reasoning\\\",\\\"content\\\":[],\\\"encrypted_content\\\":\\\"gAAAAABqJjx-VDiAt3lh3ps8my_yMKmud15VNopP8oGRthf7Eqn0Wp33eEe-RTMLAGnvN88JoBestBlNzStpq7fm4yQh6iANXtDmT0Dsbudoc6o1p-1LVArsdd62bG5FWHYKLdaP-rL4j-XJTToOrf0mG3AH9bRXRxOwCE5TazXJvLCfd4Aq51RmzOeDTiwOKnhAhOEST6sqxOEmPdMPrNuHfDBeaZ7alpjL51fZ48A_ibu1rfQn19SYN40w0pwDbgIbaBUWByU55Ds3REBeyvLjxvYdeBnNzJlMGjESb7WjDzzGQrtm44tKaIpaQR2x9_8_enrqReSopvKlGJ60QUCvYd1rVa8wMs2IryyrA49suw-xjSc_Y-3G_klxcAF0l1ufkComb0hOtAXUZMxTGoG4MR_u8fwiWu_td0CGjl6cUgzqLkNyGbrthPod1zQ9mKYvJcBQHc8Zs3HKRQZxpQzAUMHWVZdhgK2S4_afQrX-UnOQlQsxEAm2Z3orTz_xhw3Q0q9YuzqHLrJs17bKCtw2mYXI6XuczrneyDTUvEBrsLtEvutykInDy0tcXnUs-mNQG3CYLKDLwr4ahB2DXlPJBWucKE5K8IFcIQ613vG0WOR7b5Vtj5zwsCPkOlnVACkq1rKUn5v0_PzxxPIS4pG58yyrdXlttxeUKd0ElGngo2Dct_KT1zizp0JrVNxcSh4IW9kJ2xUzsLw6p_s4WzONR4XZG6SoSsAaEwVzSaDd1ZPmFC3yadMlQzTGzo4gzS18FuPGMjK4-iWTT-xjIs9ds5Qhzuu6-vufBh0Use17hsj5-wF-k8a6J4s7WZobuSgKkKH8hZxQr11b5mKyJ-GnaXh0iBIwOMEnBfvyp43gNFjcH5mQvFsrLMKgUzr1Uv_24b